<paragraph pageId="54" pageNumber="129">
<bibRefCitation author="Wolcott, AB" journalOrPublisher="Field Museum of Natural History, Zoological Series" pageId="78" pageNumber="153" pagination="339 - 401" title="Note on some Cleridae of Middle and North America with descriptions of new species." volume="7" year="1910">Wolcott (1910)</bibRefCitation>
, in his notes from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Chevrolat’s">Chevrolat's</normalizedToken>
description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chaudoir, 1879" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Macrotelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macrotelus cinctipennis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinctipennis">Macrotelus cinctipennis</taxonomicName>
, mentioned the rarity of the species; he further indicated that this species was unknown to him and he had not encountered it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
